comments: McDaniels (MIN) wraps his arm around DeRozan (CHI) and initiates contact with his arm and body, affecting his shot attempt.
Gobert (MIN) braces for the ensuing contact with Caruso (CHI) with his arms slightly extended during the screen.
Vucevic (CHI) reaches in and marginal contact occurs with Gobert (MIN) as he receives the ball in the paint.
Vucevic (CHI) leans forwards and makes contact with the ball before marginal contact occurs with Towns' (MIN) arm.
Gobert (MIN) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
Anderson (MIN) is assessed an unsportsmanlike technical foul on the bench.
Edwards (MIN) briefly places his hands on Craig's (CHI) back with little extension during the rebound.
Edwards (MIN) has his off-arm extended and briefly places it against Caruso (CHI) on the perimeter.
Gobert (MIN) establishes himself in DeRozan's (CHI) path and absorbs the contact.
Gobert (MIN) establishes himself in Caruso's (CHI) path and marginal contact occurs as they come together during the pick.
Craig (CHI) and Edwards (MIN) are moving in the same direction when Craig turns to roll and incidental contact occurs.
Craig (CHI) establishes himself in McDaniels's (MIN) path and absorbs the contact as the two come together.
Craig (CHI) contests Towns' (MIN) jump shot and the contact after the release, and follow-through, is marginal.

DeRozan (CHI) mishandles the loose ball and although McDaniels (MIN) briefly has a hand on his shoulder, the contact is marginal and does not prevent him from gathering the ball or otherwise dislodge him from his position.
Coach Donovan (CHI) signals for and is granted a timeout when Caruso (CHI) is in possession of the ball.
Conley (MIN) legally contests DeRozan's (CHI) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Edwards (MIN) initiates contact with DeRozan's (CHI) arm, which affects his shot attempt at the basket.
Gobert (MIN) is already in Caruso's (CHI) path and slightly extends his arms outward as marginal body contact occurs to Caruso as he defends over the screen.
Gobert (MIN) places his forearm to Drummond's (CHI) side and marginal body contact occurs defending his layup attempt.
Conley (MIN) establishes himself in Craig's (CHI) path and absorbs the contact as marginal contact occurs during the screen.
Craig (CHI) moves laterally into Towns' (MIN) path and initiates lower body contact that affects Towns' SQBR during the drive.

After communicating with the Replay Center, it is confirmed that White (CHI) establishes himself in a legal guarding position outside of the restricted area and is dislodged from his legally obtained position.
DeRozan (CHI) places his forearm against McDaniels (MIN) and releases from contact.
Gobert (MIN) initiates contact to Drummond's (CHI) arm and the contact affects his ability to gather the loose ball.
Drummond (CHI) initiates contact with Edwards' (MIN) wrist, which affects his driving shot attempt.

Replay review of the foul called on DeRozan (CHI) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. DeRozan (CHI) jumps vertically and absorbs the contact initiated by Edwards (MIN) during his driving shot attempt.
Gobert (MIN) initiates contact with White (CHI) during the screen and does not give him room to avoid it.
Conley (MIN) commits a take foul on DeRozan (CHI).
